{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Today I'm going to talk to you about the problem of other minds."},{"time":3000,"text":"And the problem I'm going to talk about"},{"time":5000,"text":"is not the familiar one from philosophy,"},{"time":8000,"text":"which is, \"How can we know"},{"time":10000,"text":"whether other people have minds?\""},{"time":12000,"text":"That is, maybe you have a mind,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and everyone else is just a really convincing robot."},{"time":17000,"text":"So that's a problem in philosophy,"},{"time":19000,"text":"but for today's purposes I'm going to assume"},{"time":21000,"text":"that many people in this audience have a mind,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and that I don't have to worry about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"There is a second problem that is maybe even more familiar to us"},{"time":28000,"text":"as parents and teachers and spouses"},{"time":31000,"text":"and novelists,"},{"time":33000,"text":"which is, \"Why is it so hard"},{"time":35000,"text":"to know what somebody else wants or believes?\""},{"time":37000,"text":"Or perhaps, more relevantly,"},{"time":39000,"text":"\"Why is it so hard to change what somebody else wants or believes?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"I think novelists put this best."},{"time":44000,"text":"Like Philip Roth, who said,"},{"time":46000,"text":"\"And yet, what are we to do about this terribly significant business"},{"time":49000,"text":"of other people?"},{"time":51000,"text":"So ill equipped are we all,"},{"time":53000,"text":"to envision one another's interior workings"},{"time":55000,"text":"and invisible aims.\""},{"time":57000,"text":"So as a teacher and as a spouse,"},{"time":60000,"text":"this is, of course, a problem I confront every day."},{"time":62000,"text":"But as a scientist, I'm interested in a different problem of other minds,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and that is the one I'm going to introduce to you today."},{"time":68000,"text":"And that problem is, \"How is it so easy"},{"time":70000,"text":"to know other minds?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"So to start with an illustration,"},{"time":74000,"text":"you need almost no information,"},{"time":76000,"text":"one snapshot of a stranger,"},{"time":78000,"text":"to guess what this woman is thinking,"},{"time":80000,"text":"or what this man is."},{"time":83000,"text":"And put another way, the crux of the problem is"},{"time":85000,"text":"the machine that we use for thinking about other minds,"},{"time":88000,"text":"our brain, is made up of pieces, brain cells,"},{"time":91000,"text":"that we share with all other animals, with monkeys"},{"time":93000,"text":"and mice and even sea slugs."},{"time":96000,"text":"And yet, you put them together in a particular network,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and what you get is the capacity to write Romeo and Juliet."},{"time":102000,"text":"Or to say, as Alan Greenspan did,"},{"time":104000,"text":"\"I know you think you understand what you thought I said,"},{"time":107000,"text":"but I'm not sure you realize that what you heard"},{"time":109000,"text":"is not what I meant.\""},{"time":111000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"So, the job of my field of cognitive neuroscience"},{"time":116000,"text":"is to stand with these ideas,"},{"time":118000,"text":"one in each hand."},{"time":120000,"text":"And to try to understand how you can put together"},{"time":123000,"text":"simple units, simple messages over space and time, in a network,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and get this amazing human capacity to think about minds."},{"time":131000,"text":"So I'm going to tell you three things about this today."},{"time":134000,"text":"Obviously the whole project here is huge."},{"time":137000,"text":"And I'm going to tell you just our first few steps"},{"time":140000,"text":"about the discovery of a special brain region"},{"time":142000,"text":"for thinking about other people's thoughts."},{"time":144000,"text":"Some observations on the slow development of this system"},{"time":146000,"text":"as we learn how to do this difficult job."},{"time":150000,"text":"And then finally, to show that some of the differences"},{"time":152000,"text":"between people, in how we judge others,"},{"time":155000,"text":"can be explained by differences in this brain system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"So first, the first thing I want to tell you is that"},{"time":161000,"text":"there is a brain region in the human brain, in your brains,"},{"time":164000,"text":"whose job it is to think about other people's thoughts."},{"time":167000,"text":"This is a picture of it."},{"time":169000,"text":"It's called the Right Temporo-Parietal Junction."},{"time":171000,"text":"It's above and behind your right ear."},{"time":173000,"text":"And this is the brain region you used when you saw the pictures I showed you,"},{"time":175000,"text":"or when you read Romeo and Juliet"},{"time":177000,"text":"or when you tried to understand Alan Greenspan."},{"time":180000,"text":"And you don't use it for solving any other kinds of logical problems."},{"time":184000,"text":"So this brain region is called the Right TPJ."},{"time":187000,"text":"And this picture shows the average activation"},{"time":189000,"text":"in a group of what we call typical human adults."},{"time":191000,"text":"They're MIT undergraduates."},{"time":193000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"The second thing I want to say about this brain system"},{"time":199000,"text":"is that although we human adults"},{"time":201000,"text":"are really good at understanding other minds,"},{"time":203000,"text":"we weren't always that way."},{"time":205000,"text":"It takes children a long time to break into the system."},{"time":208000,"text":"I'm going to show you a little bit of that long, extended process."},{"time":212000,"text":"The first thing I'm going to show you is a change between age three and five,"},{"time":215000,"text":"as kids learn to understand"},{"time":217000,"text":"that somebody else can have beliefs that are different from their own."},{"time":220000,"text":"So I'm going to show you a five-year-old"},{"time":222000,"text":"who is getting a standard kind of puzzle"},{"time":224000,"text":"that we call the false belief task."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Rebecca Saxe (Video): This is the first pirate. His name is Ivan."},{"time":230000,"text":"And you know what pirates really like?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"Child: What? RS: Pirates really like cheese sandwiches."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Child: Cheese? I love cheese!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"RS: Yeah. So Ivan has this cheese sandwich,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and he says, \"Yum yum yum yum yum!"},{"time":242000,"text":"I really love cheese sandwiches.\""},{"time":244000,"text":"And Ivan puts his sandwich over here, on top of the pirate chest."},{"time":248000,"text":"And Ivan says, \"You know what? I need a drink with my lunch.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"And so Ivan goes to get a drink."},{"time":255000,"text":"And while Ivan is away"},{"time":257000,"text":"the wind comes,"},{"time":260000,"text":"and it blows the sandwich down onto the grass."},{"time":262000,"text":"And now, here comes the other pirate."},{"time":266000,"text":"This pirate is called Joshua."},{"time":269000,"text":"And Joshua also really loves cheese sandwiches."},{"time":271000,"text":"So Joshua has a cheese sandwich and he says,"},{"time":273000,"text":"\"Yum yum yum yum yum! I love cheese sandwiches.\""},{"time":277000,"text":"And he puts his cheese sandwich over here on top of the pirate chest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"Child: So, that one is his."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"RS: That one is Joshua's. That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Child: And then his went on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"RS: That's exactly right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"Child: So he won't know which one is his."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"RS: Oh. So now Joshua goes off to get a drink."},{"time":293000,"text":"Ivan comes back and he says, \"I want my cheese sandwich.\""},{"time":297000,"text":"So which one do you think Ivan is going to take?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"Child: I think he is going to take that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"RS: Yeah, you think he's going to take that one? All right. Let's see."},{"time":304000,"text":"Oh yeah, you were right. He took that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307000,"text":"So that's a five-year-old who clearly understands"},{"time":309000,"text":"that other people can have false beliefs"},{"time":311000,"text":"and what the consequences are for their actions."},{"time":313000,"text":"Now I'm going to show you a three-year-old"},{"time":316000,"text":"who got the same puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"RS: And Ivan says, \"I want my cheese sandwich.\""},{"time":320000,"text":"Which sandwich is he going to take?"},{"time":323000,"text":"Do you think he's going to take that one? Let's see what happens."},{"time":325000,"text":"Let's see what he does. Here comes Ivan."},{"time":327000,"text":"And he says, \"I want my cheese sandwich.\""},{"time":330000,"text":"And he takes this one."},{"time":332000,"text":"Uh-oh. Why did he take that one?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335000,"text":"Child: His was on the grass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"So the three-year-old does two things differently."},{"time":342000,"text":"First, he predicts Ivan will take the sandwich"},{"time":345000,"text":"that's really his."},{"time":347000,"text":"And second, when he sees Ivan taking the sandwich where he left his,"},{"time":351000,"text":"where we would say he's taking that one because he thinks it's his,"},{"time":354000,"text":"the three-year-old comes up with another explanation:"},{"time":357000,"text":"He's not taking his own sandwich because he doesn't want it,"},{"time":359000,"text":"because now it's dirty, on the ground."},{"time":361000,"text":"So that's why he's taking the other sandwich."},{"time":363000,"text":"Now of course, development doesn't end at five."},{"time":367000,"text":"And we can see the continuation of this process"},{"time":369000,"text":"of learning to think about other people's thoughts"},{"time":371000,"text":"by upping the ante"},{"time":373000,"text":"and asking children now, not for an action prediction,"},{"time":376000,"text":"but for a moral judgment."},{"time":378000,"text":"So first I'm going to show you the three-year-old again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"RS.: So is Ivan being mean and naughty for taking Joshua's sandwich?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"Child: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"RS: Should Ivan get in trouble for taking Joshua's sandwich?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":387000,"text":"Child: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"So it's maybe not surprising he thinks it was mean of Ivan"},{"time":391000,"text":"to take Joshua's sandwich,"},{"time":393000,"text":"since he thinks Ivan only took Joshua's sandwich"},{"time":395000,"text":"to avoid having to eat his own dirty sandwich."},{"time":398000,"text":"But now I'm going to show you the five-year-old."},{"time":400000,"text":"Remember the five-year-old completely understood"},{"time":402000,"text":"why Ivan took Joshua's sandwich."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"RS: Was Ivan being mean and naughty"},{"time":406000,"text":"for taking Joshua's sandwich?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"Child: Um, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"And so, it is not until age seven"},{"time":412000,"text":"that we get what looks more like an adult response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"RS: Should Ivan get in trouble for taking Joshua's sandwich?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"Child: No, because the wind should get in trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"He says the wind should get in trouble"},{"time":423000,"text":"for switching the sandwiches."},{"time":425000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"And now what we've started to do in my lab"},{"time":429000,"text":"is to put children into the brain scanner"},{"time":431000,"text":"and ask what's going on in their brain"},{"time":434000,"text":"as they develop this ability to think about other people's thoughts."},{"time":437000,"text":"So the first thing is that in children we see this same brain region, the Right TPJ,"},{"time":441000,"text":"being used while children are thinking about other people."},{"time":444000,"text":"But it's not quite like the adult brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"So whereas in the adults, as I told you,"},{"time":448000,"text":"this brain region is almost completely specialized --"},{"time":451000,"text":"it does almost nothing else except for thinking about other people's thoughts --"},{"time":454000,"text":"in children it's much less so,"},{"time":456000,"text":"when they are age five to eight,"},{"time":458000,"text":"the age range of the children I just showed you."},{"time":460000,"text":"And actually if we even look at eight to 11-year-olds,"},{"time":463000,"text":"getting into early adolescence,"},{"time":465000,"text":"they still don't have quite an adult-like brain region."},{"time":468000,"text":"And so, what we can see is that over the course of childhood"},{"time":471000,"text":"and even into adolescence,"},{"time":473000,"text":"both the cognitive system,"},{"time":475000,"text":"our mind's ability to think about other minds,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and the brain system that supports it"},{"time":479000,"text":"are continuing, slowly, to develop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"But of course, as you're probably aware,"},{"time":484000,"text":"even in adulthood,"},{"time":486000,"text":"people differ from one another in how good they are"},{"time":488000,"text":"at thinking of other minds, how often they do it"},{"time":490000,"text":"and how accurately."},{"time":492000,"text":"And so what we wanted to know was, could differences among adults"},{"time":495000,"text":"in how they think about other people's thoughts"},{"time":497000,"text":"be explained in terms of differences in this brain region?"},{"time":500000,"text":"So, the first thing that we did is we gave adults a version"},{"time":503000,"text":"of the pirate problem that we gave to the kids."},{"time":505000,"text":"And I'm going to give that to you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"So Grace and her friend are on a tour of a chemical factory,"},{"time":510000,"text":"and they take a break for coffee."},{"time":512000,"text":"And Grace's friend asks for some sugar in her coffee."},{"time":515000,"text":"Grace goes to make the coffee"},{"time":518000,"text":"and finds by the coffee a pot"},{"time":520000,"text":"containing a white powder, which is sugar."},{"time":523000,"text":"But the powder is labeled \"Deadly Poison,\""},{"time":526000,"text":"so Grace thinks that the powder is a deadly poison."},{"time":529000,"text":"And she puts it in her friend's coffee."},{"time":531000,"text":"And her friend drinks the coffee, and is fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534000,"text":"How many people think it was morally permissible"},{"time":536000,"text":"for Grace to put the powder in the coffee?"},{"time":540000,"text":"Okay. Good. (Laughter)"},{"time":543000,"text":"So we ask people, how much should Grace be blamed"},{"time":546000,"text":"in this case, which we call a failed attempt to harm?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"And we can compare that to another case,"},{"time":550000,"text":"where everything in the real world is the same."},{"time":552000,"text":"The powder is still sugar, but what's different is what Grace thinks."},{"time":555000,"text":"Now she thinks the powder is sugar."},{"time":558000,"text":"And perhaps unsurprisingly, if Grace thinks the powder is sugar"},{"time":561000,"text":"and puts it in her friend's coffee,"},{"time":563000,"text":"people say she deserves no blame at all."},{"time":565000,"text":"Whereas if she thinks the powder was poison, even though it's really sugar,"},{"time":569000,"text":"now people say she deserves a lot of blame,"},{"time":572000,"text":"even though what happened in the real world was exactly the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"And in fact, they say she deserves more blame"},{"time":577000,"text":"in this case, the failed attempt to harm,"},{"time":579000,"text":"than in another case,"},{"time":581000,"text":"which we call an accident."},{"time":583000,"text":"Where Grace thought the powder was sugar,"},{"time":585000,"text":"because it was labeled \"sugar\" and by the coffee machine,"},{"time":587000,"text":"but actually the powder was poison."},{"time":589000,"text":"So even though when the powder was poison,"},{"time":592000,"text":"the friend drank the coffee and died,"},{"time":595000,"text":"people say Grace deserves less blame in that case,"},{"time":598000,"text":"when she innocently thought it was sugar,"},{"time":600000,"text":"than in the other case, where she thought it was poison"},{"time":602000,"text":"and no harm occurred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"People, though, disagree a little bit"},{"time":607000,"text":"about exactly how much blame Grace should get"},{"time":609000,"text":"in the accident case."},{"time":611000,"text":"Some people think she should deserve more blame,"},{"time":613000,"text":"and other people less."},{"time":615000,"text":"And what I'm going to show you is what happened when we look inside"},{"time":617000,"text":"the brains of people while they're making that judgment."},{"time":619000,"text":"So what I'm showing you, from left to right,"},{"time":621000,"text":"is how much activity there was in this brain region,"},{"time":624000,"text":"and from top to bottom, how much blame"},{"time":626000,"text":"people said that Grace deserved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"And what you can see is, on the left"},{"time":630000,"text":"when there was very little activity in this brain region,"},{"time":632000,"text":"people paid little attention to her innocent belief"},{"time":635000,"text":"and said she deserved a lot of blame for the accident."},{"time":638000,"text":"Whereas on the right, where there was a lot of activity,"},{"time":640000,"text":"people paid a lot more attention to her innocent belief,"},{"time":643000,"text":"and said she deserved a lot less blame"},{"time":645000,"text":"for causing the accident."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"So that's good, but of course"},{"time":649000,"text":"what we'd rather is have a way to interfere"},{"time":651000,"text":"with function in this brain region,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and see if we could change people's moral judgment."},{"time":656000,"text":"And we do have such a tool."},{"time":658000,"text":"It's called Trans-Cranial Magnetic Stimulation,"},{"time":660000,"text":"or TMS."},{"time":662000,"text":"This is a tool that lets us pass a magnetic pulse"},{"time":664000,"text":"through somebody's skull, into a small region of their brain,"},{"time":668000,"text":"and temporarily disorganize the function of the neurons in that region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"So I'm going to show you a demo of this."},{"time":674000,"text":"First, I'm going to show you that this is a magnetic pulse."},{"time":677000,"text":"I'm going to show you what happens when you put a quarter on the machine."},{"time":680000,"text":"When you hear clicks, we're turning the machine on."},{"time":690000,"text":"So now I'm going to apply that same pulse to my brain,"},{"time":693000,"text":"to the part of my brain that controls my hand."},{"time":695000,"text":"So there is no physical force, just a magnetic pulse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Woman (Video): Ready, Rebecca? RS: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"Okay, so it causes a small involuntary contraction in my hand"},{"time":708000,"text":"by putting a magnetic pulse in my brain."},{"time":711000,"text":"And we can use that same pulse,"},{"time":713000,"text":"now applied to the RTPJ,"},{"time":715000,"text":"to ask if we can change people's moral judgments."},{"time":718000,"text":"So these are the judgments I showed you before, people's normal moral judgments."},{"time":720000,"text":"And then we can apply TMS to the RTPJ"},{"time":723000,"text":"and ask how people's judgments change."},{"time":725000,"text":"And the first thing is, people can still do this task overall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"So their judgments of the case when everything was fine"},{"time":731000,"text":"remain the same. They say she deserves no blame."},{"time":734000,"text":"But in the case of a failed attempt to harm,"},{"time":738000,"text":"where Grace thought that it was poison, although it was really sugar,"},{"time":741000,"text":"people now say it was more okay, she deserves less blame"},{"time":744000,"text":"for putting the powder in the coffee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"And in the case of the accident, where she thought that it was sugar,"},{"time":749000,"text":"but it was really poison and so she caused a death,"},{"time":752000,"text":"people say that it was less okay, she deserves more blame."},{"time":758000,"text":"So what I've told you today is that"},{"time":760000,"text":"people come, actually, especially well equipped"},{"time":764000,"text":"to think about other people's thoughts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"We have a special brain system"},{"time":768000,"text":"that lets us think about what other people are thinking."},{"time":771000,"text":"This system takes a long time to develop,"},{"time":773000,"text":"slowly throughout the course of childhood and into early adolescence."},{"time":776000,"text":"And even in adulthood, differences in this brain region"},{"time":779000,"text":"can explain differences among adults"},{"time":781000,"text":"in how we think about and judge other people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784000,"text":"But I want to give the last word back to the novelists,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and to Philip Roth, who ended by saying,"},{"time":790000,"text":"\"The fact remains that getting people right"},{"time":792000,"text":"is not what living is all about anyway."},{"time":794000,"text":"It's getting them wrong that is living."},{"time":796000,"text":"Getting them wrong and wrong and wrong,"},{"time":799000,"text":"and then on careful reconsideration,"},{"time":801000,"text":"getting them wrong again.\""},{"time":803000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":805000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"Chris Anderson: So, I have a question. When you start talking about using"},{"time":817000,"text":"magnetic pulses to change people's moral judgments,"},{"time":820000,"text":"that sounds alarming."},{"time":823000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":824000,"text":"Please tell me that you're not taking phone calls from the Pentagon, say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"RS: I'm not."},{"time":830000,"text":"I mean, they're calling, but I'm not taking the call."},{"time":833000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834000,"text":"CA: They really are calling?"},{"time":836000,"text":"So then seriously,"},{"time":839000,"text":"you must lie awake at night sometimes"},{"time":842000,"text":"wondering where this work leads."},{"time":844000,"text":"I mean, you're clearly an incredible human being,"},{"time":846000,"text":"but someone could take this knowledge"},{"time":849000,"text":"and in some future"},{"time":851000,"text":"not-torture chamber,"},{"time":853000,"text":"do acts that people here might be worried about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"RS: Yeah, we worry about this."},{"time":858000,"text":"So, there's a couple of things to say about TMS."},{"time":861000,"text":"One is that you can't be TMSed without knowing it."},{"time":863000,"text":"So it's not a surreptitious technology."},{"time":866000,"text":"It's quite hard, actually, to get those very small changes."},{"time":869000,"text":"The changes I showed you are impressive to me"},{"time":872000,"text":"because of what they tell us about the function of the brain,"},{"time":874000,"text":"but they're small on the scale"},{"time":876000,"text":"of the moral judgments that we actually make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"And what we changed was not people's"},{"time":880000,"text":"moral judgments when they're deciding what to do,"},{"time":883000,"text":"when they're making action choices."},{"time":885000,"text":"We changed their ability to judge other people's actions."},{"time":888000,"text":"And so, I think of what I'm doing not so much as"},{"time":890000,"text":"studying the defendant in a criminal trial,"},{"time":892000,"text":"but studying the jury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"CA: Is your work going to lead to any recommendations"},{"time":897000,"text":"in education, to perhaps bring up"},{"time":900000,"text":"a generation of kids able to make fairer moral judgments?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"RS: That's one of the idealistic hopes."},{"time":908000,"text":"The whole research program here of studying"},{"time":912000,"text":"the distinctive parts of the human brain is brand new."},{"time":916000,"text":"Until recently, what we knew about the brain"},{"time":918000,"text":"were the things that any other animal's brain could do too,"},{"time":921000,"text":"so we could study it in animal models."},{"time":923000,"text":"We knew how brains see, and how they control the body"},{"time":925000,"text":"and how they hear and sense."},{"time":927000,"text":"And the whole project of understanding"},{"time":930000,"text":"how brains do the uniquely human things --"},{"time":932000,"text":"learn language and abstract concepts,"},{"time":935000,"text":"and thinking about other people's thoughts -- that's brand new."},{"time":937000,"text":"And we don't know yet what the implications will be"},{"time":939000,"text":"of understanding it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"CA: So I've got one last question. There is this thing called"},{"time":943000,"text":"the hard problem of consciousness,"},{"time":945000,"text":"that puzzles a lot of people."},{"time":947000,"text":"The notion that you can understand"},{"time":950000,"text":"why a brain works, perhaps."},{"time":952000,"text":"But why does anyone have to feel anything?"},{"time":955000,"text":"Why does it seem to require these beings who sense things"},{"time":958000,"text":"for us to operate?"},{"time":960000,"text":"You're a brilliant young neuroscientist."},{"time":963000,"text":"I mean, what chances do you think there are"},{"time":965000,"text":"that at some time in your career,"},{"time":967000,"text":"someone, you or someone else,"},{"time":969000,"text":"is going to come up with some paradigm shift"},{"time":971000,"text":"in understanding what seems an impossible problem?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"RS: I hope they do. And I think they probably won't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979000,"text":"CA: Why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"RS: It's not called the hard problem of consciousness for nothing."},{"time":985000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"CA: That's a great answer. Rebecca Saxe, thank you very much. That was fantastic."},{"time":990000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}